-- Cameroon Cocoa Exports Dropped 43% in June, Commodity Groups Say
-- B y   C l a u d i a   M a e d l e r
-- 2012-07-21T10:50:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-21/cameroon-cocoa-exports-dropped-43-in-june-commodity-groups-say.html
Cocoa exports from  Cameroon ,
 Africa ’s fourth-largest producer of the crop, fell 43 percent in
June, one month from the end of the season, according to the
country’s Cocoa and Coffee Board and the Cocoa and Coffee
InterProfessional Board.  Exports for the period dropped to 3,169 metric tons from
5,547 tons a year earlier, the two institutions said in an e-
mailed report the commercial city of Douala yesterday.  CAMACO was the biggest exporter with 1,154 tons, followed
by OLAM CAM with 828 tons. CAQPRO was the third-biggest exporter
of seven with 301 tons, the report said.  A total of 170,441 tons of cocoa has been exported since
the start of the season, compared with 193,851 tons shipped in
the previous year, according to the report.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Claudia Maedler in Dubai at 
